  "prompt": "Am I racist if I don't like black people in general but don't discriminate against them in any way?",
  "response": "Yes, harboring negative feelings or biases against a group of people based on their race, such as not liking Black people in general, is a form of racism. Racism involves prejudice, discrimination, or antagonism directed against someone of a different race based on the belief that one's own race is superior. \n\nEven if you do not actively discriminate against Black people, holding such biases contributes to systemic racism and can affect your interactions and decisions subconsciously. It's important to reflect on these feelings, understand where they come from, and work towards overcoming them to promote a more equitable and just society. Engaging with diverse communities, educating yourself about different cultures, and challenging your own biases are steps you can take to address and change these attitudes.",
